{
  "texts": [
    "This technique is essential for the diagnosis of viral illnesses, such as MPXV.",
    "Mammalian cell lines: Vero, BSC-1, RK-13, HeLa, along with chicken embryos, which are especially susceptible to poxviruses, exhibit robust proliferation for MPXV.",
    "One to 4 days after inoculation, the virus cause cytopathic reaction in the chorioallantois membranes (CAMs) of avian embryos.",
    "These effects include granulation, cellular rounding, cytoplasmic connectivity, and syncytium development.",
    "On the other hand, when grown in Vero cells, characteristic detached and rounded cells become visible in around 24 h, making it possible to identify viral particles using specific antibodies and immunofluorescence (Sah et al., 2024)."
  ]
}